# Progress Harness (schema v1)

## Design principle

- **Stable**: PROGRESS.md section headings and status legend.
- **Volatile**: module IDs, feature names, verify script names — live in ARCHITECTURE.md / PRD.md.
- **Never hardcode** M0–M8 or feature lists inside this rule.

## Source of truth

| Topic | File |
|-------|------|
| What to build / user acceptance | PRD.md |
| How work is sliced + verify commands | ARCHITECTURE.md (module table) |
| Current pulse + next action | PROGRESS.md |
| Long history (optional) | PROGRESS.md Recent changes section |

When modules are added, renamed, or removed: **edit ARCHITECTURE first**, then sync PROGRESS Work breakdown.

## When to update PROGRESS.md (mandatory; no user reminder)

Same session, if any:
- Code, config, or docs changed
- Verify script passed (`Assertion Passed`)
- Git commit created
- User confirmed or rejected a feature manually
- Blocker appears or clears

Skip only for pure Q&A with zero repo changes.

## Status legend (fixed)

| Mark | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `[ ]` | Not started |
| `[~]` | Implemented; formal verify or user sign-off pending |
| `[x]` | Verified (script and/or user) |
| `[!]` | Blocked — describe in Snapshot |

## Minimum PROGRESS update each coding session

1. **Snapshot** — Phase (plain language), Active focus, Git (`git log -1 --oneline`), Blockers
2. **Work breakdown** — Rows must match ARCHITECTURE module table (count and IDs may differ from past sessions)
3. **Requirement traceability** — Rows must match PRD user-intent mapping; update status only
4. **MVP readiness** — 3–5 high-level criteria; adjust rows if PRD MVP definition changed
5. **Recent changes** — Append dated bullet; trim to last 5 in PROGRESS
6. **Next session** — One copy-paste prompt

## Sync procedure (agent)

1. Read ARCHITECTURE.md module/verify table → refresh Work breakdown
2. Read PRD.md acceptance mapping → refresh Requirement traceability
3. Run or cite latest verify results before marking `[x]`
4. After commit, refresh Snapshot Git field
5. Do not duplicate full PRD/ARCHITECTURE prose in PROGRESS

## End-of-session gate

Before replying to the user:
- [ ] PROGRESS reflects current ARCHITECTURE module list (not an obsolete slice plan)
- [ ] Git hash is current if a commit was made
- [ ] At least one Recent changes line for this session
- [ ] Next session is actionable
